55.7	Wear_Sunscreen	Wear Sunscreen	The essay was used in its entirety by Australian film director Baz Luhrmann on his 1998 album Something for Everybody, as "Everybody's Free (To Wear Sunscreen)". The song sampled Luhrmann's remixed version of the song "Everybody's Free (To Feel Good)" by Rozalla. Subsequently released as a single, the song opened with the words "Ladies and Gentlemen of the Class of '99".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6c/Everybody%27sfreetowearsunscreen.jpg
